                  <Abstract ID="Abs1" Language="En">

                     <Heading>Abstract.</Heading>

                     <Para> We study the convergence rates of solutions to drift-diffusion systems (arising from plasma, semiconductors and electrolytes theories) to their self-similar or steady states. This analysis involves entropy-type Lyapunov functionals and logarithmic Sobolev inequalities.</Para>

